lent for linguistic obfuscation. Between adulation and disdain must lie a balanced picture of Fuller's life and his work. This volume paints that picture by taking a broader historical view, discussing Fuller and his work in the context of larger social and cultural patterns. Fuller is a common thread in a critical cultural history that will show him to be both a participant in and a product of his times. By placing Fuller and his work in a historical framework, we will arrive at a much richer understanding of both this self-made polymath and his times. This fresh, contextual look at Fuller's work from leading scholars in different fields is an important step toward filling the void of serious scholarship on Fuller.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aTechnology & Engineering / History.2bisacsh1 aChu, Hsiao-Yun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChu, Hsiao-Yun, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGough, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Barry M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrausse, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLichtenstein, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Reinhold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMassey, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNye, David E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, Felicity D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegal, Howard P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrujillo, Roberto G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrujillo, Roberto G.,